Package: BzeaSeq
Type: Package
Title: Teosinte Introgression Analysis for Maize Genomics
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Fausto", "Rodriguez-Zapata", , "frodrig4@ncsu.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8088-1113"))
Description: A comprehensive toolkit for analyzing teosinte introgressions in maize
    Near Isogenic Lines (NILs). Provides functions for processing GATK allelic counts,
    performing ancestry classification using clustering and Hidden Markov Models,
    extracting introgression segments, and creating visualizations. Designed for
    BC2S3 and other structured breeding populations with expected Mendelian ratios.
    Includes specialized functions for handling large-scale genomic data and
    creating publication-ready plots of introgression patterns.
